340
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:55,640
Meirav, this isn't really comfortable for me.

341
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,160
Suffer quietly, it's just a coffee thing.

342
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,800
It's them. Get it together.

343
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,640
Alin, to the women's section.

344
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:11,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

345
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:12,920
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

346
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:17,599
Shabbat...
-Shabbat Shalom.

347
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:20,119
Shabana. Shabana, please, Shabana.

348
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:23,880
God have mercy. May God save us...

349
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:28,520
Mom, can I talk to you for a second in the kitchen?

350
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:39,960
Is this the match? We dressed up for this?

351
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:42,600
Are you talking?
-It's not funny.

352
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:46,120
When I was in the women's section and looked down
that guy was standing next to someone handsome.

353
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:49,760
I'm with you for seven days. I think
it was a trap by his mom.

354
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:52,720
Why do you dismiss right away?
-I'm not dismissing.

355
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:56,200
It's him who's cross-eyed.
-Everyone who's cross-eyed, in his own way.

356
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,680
Leave her alone, enough. She's nervous.
-No, I'm not.

357
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:04,640
Maybe under all that cross-eyed appearance
there's a handsome prince hiding...

358
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,960
Okay, enough with the jokes.
How do we get rid of them?

359
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,960
How did my socks get over there?
-You need to cut with a cutting knife,

360
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,080
