-What "cut"?

361
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:17,000
If it breaks, the carpet will tear.
And there's no spare white one left.

362
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,920
Well, this part is staying under the bed anyway,

363
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:22,960
So come on, let it stay a little bump.
-What "little bump"?

364
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:26,320
It's a tsunami. Moshe, seriously.
-What, come on...

365
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:29,840
Come on. What, here, here. Here. Okay?

366
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,560
Better? Flat enough? Here.

367
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:36,120
Here you go.
-Did you see Justin Bieber?

368
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,440
Justin Bieber?
-Her hamster.

369
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,280
Because he's running that way.
-Hamster?

370
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:46,960
No. No, sweetie. We didn't see him.

371
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:52,360
No! No!

372
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,680
No, Justin. No!

373
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:00,480
Why? No! No!

374
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:04,000
No! No!

375
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:14,600
Well...
-I killed him!

376
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,680
I killed Justin Bieber, I killed him.

377
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,600
Moshe!
-I killed him.

378
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,360
Mouse! Mouse!
-You killed him.

379
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:25,920
I killed him. A lot,
Where are you? I killed him.

380
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,960
Can't we leave him there?
-If we leave the hamster here, it'll stink.

381
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:34,560
Well, then there's no choice.
We'll go for a cut and hope for the best.

382
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:38,760
Wow, wow. Bravo! Bravo!
I see you finished.

383
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:40,360
Wonderful
Ar
In

384
