-Is he alive?

387
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:52,240
Recently he ran by the bathroom,
running free.

388
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:53,880
Yeah, yeah. Come, come, come!

389
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:57,680
The hamster is alive?
-So it must really be Moshe's socks.

390
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:04,560
Probably.

391
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,360
We told you there would be laughs in the end.

392
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,680
Great, laugh.

393
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:14,560
You know, Meirav,
there are whole other sectors you haven't tried.

394
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:19,800
Enough! Enough. Maybe instead of laughing and bothering
someone will find that hamster.

395
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,760
Here he is, the sweet one.
-Shai...

396
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,800
He's a bit scared. Don't worry, Justin.

397
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:31,560
You're in good hands.
-Good job, Dr. Dolittle.

398
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:35,000
You said I'm good with animals.
-How cute...

399
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,240
Come on, let's go see the room.

400
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,280
Don't bring him near me, Moshe.

401
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:41,280
I told you that part comes out from under the bed.

402
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,480
They’ll never notice.

403
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:47,200
We cleaned up.
-How nice!

404
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,120
Amazing!

405
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:51,800
In style!

406
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:55,080
Well, I understand I lost the bet.
-Partially.

407
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:58,480
You were right about the spare.
-What’s that smell?

408
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,960
It's... it's... Moshe's clothes.

409
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:04,480
He forgot them here so I...

410
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:08,640
Why? Why is the bed shaking?

411
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:09,880
The bed is shaking?

412
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:11,360
Yeah.
-Look, the clothes are outside.

413
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,040
Yeah, but the smell remains.

414
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:16,880
It... it smells like Moshe's essence.

415
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,880
The bed is shaking.

416
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:24,080
Maybe we really lost the bet.

417
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:25,960
Probably.

418
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,960
I'm done. I didn't even eat from the mezilof in the end.

419
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:35,040
My head hurts from the glue smell
and from... Moshe's essence.

420
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:38,720
Why? It was a fun Shabbat.
-That didn't end. At 00:21 the hatch opens,

421
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,400
Manny and I need to go buy
some PVC pipes for the repairs.

422
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:44,040
What, did you lose the bet?
-Yeah, but it's Moshe's fault.

423
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:47,160
Well, now Moshe has a different role.
-I don't get it. Why did you let him off?

424
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:50,040
For his part in the disaster?
-Why? Because he took Justin Bieber, maybe.

425
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:53,160
Uh... what... he's really not here.
-Right.

426
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:57,040
When Abu was about to leave and the girls came to get him,
Moshe started crying,

427
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:59,480
so they let him off. I don't know,
maybe because he was half-naked.

428
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:02,040
Who are you always spinning around?
-Orna.

429
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:03,960
What does she want?
-She wants to kill me,

430
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:05,000
